This is one of those things where I see what you aim for (long overblown containment procedures that get increasingly absurd and surreal to elicit humor), but only a few of these instructions got anything more than a smirk out of me. I feel like SCP-100000-J did it in a much more tightly-knit fashion (even if I didn't enjoy that one much). I think this one also tries to go for too much gross-out humor for no value out of it. I'm not particularly a fan of gross-out humor.

The thing I think I liked the most was Kate Bush's appearance in scolding the three men, but there's a logistics problem; if this is to be done every 30 minutes, how does she have time to do anything else? Surely the world would take notice.





